strategy: Adopt a mixed strategy where the row player chooses Action A with probability 0.6 and Action B with probability 0.4. This leverages the asymmetry in the Battle of Sexes game where the row player benefits from coordination when both choose the same action. By randomizing, the row player deters the column player from exploiting predictable choices, increasing expected payoff through strategic unpredictability.
